<distribution-code display="yes">I</distribution-code><congress display="yes">119th CONGRESS</congress><session display="yes">1st Session</session><legis-num display="yes">H. R. 3993</legis-num><current-chamber>IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES</current-chamber><action display="yes"><action-date date="20250612">June 12, 2025</action-date><action-desc><sponsor name-id="P000608">Mr. Peters</sponsor> (for himself, <cosponsor name-id="P000197">Ms. Pelosi</cosponsor>, <cosponsor name-id="T000472">Mr. Takano</cosponsor>, <cosponsor name-id="V000130">Mr. Vargas</cosponsor>, <cosponsor name-id="J000288">Mr. Johnson of Georgia</cosponsor>, <cosponsor name-id="T000487">Ms. Tokuda</cosponsor>, <cosponsor name-id="C001125">Mr. Carter of Louisiana</cosponsor>, <cosponsor name-id="K000391">Mr. Krishnamoorthi</cosponsor>, <cosponsor name-id="N000147">Ms. Norton</cosponsor>, <cosponsor name-id="G000559">Mr. Garamendi</cosponsor>, <cosponsor name-id="J000305">Ms. Jacobs</cosponsor>, <cosponsor name-id="S001156">Ms. Sánchez</cosponsor>, and <cosponsor name-id="L000593">Mr. Levin</cosponsor>) introduced the following bill; which was referred to the <committee-name committee-id="HAS00">Committee on Armed Services</committee-name></action-desc></action><legis-type>A BILL</legis-type><official-title display="yes">To prohibit the Secretary of the Navy from changing the names of certain naval vessels.</official-title></form><legis-body id="H96809436205446BDAF40394E49507E2D" style="OLC"> 
<section id="HE6DDDAC0BE414A3C83481EBAA2990C49" section-type="section-one"><enum>1.</enum><header>Short title</header>
 <text display-inline="no-display-inline">This Act may be cited as the <quote><short-title>Preserving Great Americans’ Legacies Act of 2025</short-title></quote>.</text></section> 
<section id="H9FC6917F9A814D268405BB699818964B"><enum>2.</enum><header>Prohibition on name change of certain naval vessels</header> 
<subsection id="H3B7E9666AF5F4F23B53973AB2DA4D0F3"><enum>(a)</enum><header>In general</header><text display-inline="yes-display-inline">Notwithstanding section 8662(b) of title 10, United States Code, the Secretary of the Navy may not change the name of any naval vessel that, as of the date of the enactment of this Act, is named after an individual referred to in subsection (b).</text></subsection> <subsection id="H3F40C0F153D24ED399F4222752E62C4D"><enum>(b)</enum><header>Individuals</header><text>An individual referred to in this subsection is any of the following:</text> 
<paragraph id="H827CA44DAFF04E44A99AE0E8D9CECCF5"><enum>(1)</enum><text>Cesar Chavez.</text></paragraph> <paragraph id="H43C4841ACC12460989E04605DD6D4CC6"> <enum>(2)</enum> <text>Medgar Evers.</text>
                </paragraph> 
<paragraph id="HF0054ADB1B0F432888136CAD031BC27A"><enum>(3)</enum><text>Ruth Bader Ginsburg.</text></paragraph> <paragraph id="HA61D0297B4854262867A38F4507E3FFB"><enum>(4)</enum><text>Dolores Huerta.</text></paragraph> 
<paragraph id="H0657B442C7EE453580B17D0CB8512BF3"><enum>(5)</enum><text display-inline="yes-display-inline">Thurgood Marshall.</text></paragraph> <paragraph id="HF6167FBC5EF840A0BDC540FAC4A602A9"><enum>(6)</enum><text>Harvey Milk.</text></paragraph> 
<paragraph id="H2C3F31C5DBA846D6BFCE823B2BF5FBBD"><enum>(7)</enum><text>Lucy Stone.</text></paragraph> <paragraph id="HFA1A7410DBE641DCB8E5BF8F3B73374F"><enum>(8)</enum><text>Harriet Tubman.</text></paragraph></subsection></section> 
